Sheep pox and goat pox, Kazakhstan
----------------------------------
Information received on 23 Dec 2009 from Dr Akhmetzhan Akievich
Sultanov, vice chairman, Committee of State Inspection, Ministry of
Agriculture, Astana, Kazakhstan

Summary
Report type Immediate notification
Start date 23 Nov 2009
Date of 1st confirmation of the event 25 Nov 2009
Report date 23 Dec 2009
Date submitted to OIE 23 Dec 2009
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence January 2002
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Sheep pox virus
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, Laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1 Jeana-Kurlys, Kachirsky, Pavlodar
Date of start of the outbreak 23 Nov 2009
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Village

Species Sheep
Susceptible 486
Cases 98
Deaths 16
Destroyed 82
Slaughtered 0

Affected Population. Clinical signs: inappetence, fever and skin lesions.
Summary of outbreaks Total outbreaks: 1

Outbreak statistics
Species Sheep
Apparent morbidity rate 20.16 percent
Apparent mortality rate 3.29 percent
Apparent case fatality rate 16.33 percent
Proportion susceptible animals lost* 20.16 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction
and/or slaughter

Epidemiology. Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection.
Unknown or inconclusive

Control measures: Measures applied. Quarantine; Movement control
inside the country; Screening; Zoning; Disinfection of infected
premises/establishment(s); Modified stamping out; No treatment of
affected animals

Vaccination in response to the outbreak (s);
Administrative division Pavlodar
Species Sheep
Total Vaccinated 486
Details Live vaccine applied around the outbreak

Measures to be applied: No other measures

Laboratory name and type Biological Security Research Institute
(National laboratory)
Species Sheep
Test agar-gel immunodiffusion (AGID)
Test date 25 Nov 2009
Result Positive

Species Sheep
Test electron microscopy
Test date 25 Nov 2009
Result Positive

Species Sheep
Test enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) 2
Test date 5 Nov 2009
Result Positive

Species Sheep
Test polymerase chain reaction (PCR)
Test date 25 Nov 2009
Result Positive

Laboratory name and type National Center of Monitoring, Reference,
Laboratory Diagnostics and Methodology in Veterinary, Astana
(National laboratory)
Species Sheep
Test agar-gel immunodiffusion (AGID)
Test date 25 Nov 2009
Result Positive

Species Sheep
Test virus neutralisation test (VNT)
Test date 25 Nov 2009
Result Positive

Laboratory name and type Pavlodar Veterinary Laboratory (National laboratory)
Species Sheep
Test agar-gel immunodiffusion (AGID)
Test date 25 Nov 2009
Result Positive

Future Reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

